        <name>HWSPINLOCK_CTX_INITIALIZER</name>
        <initializer>	{                                                                                          \
		.lock = {},                                                                        \
	}</initializer>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Initializer for a hwspinlock_ctx_t. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>We must declare each field individually because a struct <ref refid="structk__spinlock" kindref="compound">k_spinlock</ref> might have no field depending on Kconfig options, and gcc requires struct without any field to be initialized explicitly, instead of just being able to do <computeroutput>{0}</computeroutput>. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
